function create folder on signup:

curl -X GET http://<your-domain-or-ip>/init-store \
  -H "storeId: your-store-id" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-auth-token"



post for upload image:
// add the domain of the vps on the response too

curl -X POST "http://localhost:5000/upload/image" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-secret-token" \
  -F "storeId=store123" \
  -F "file=@aks.jpg"


DELETE image:

curl -X DELETE "http://localhost:5000/delete/image" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-secret-token" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"storeId": "store123", "filename": "product.jpg"}'


GET list images:

curl -X GET "http://91.216.104.8:5000/images/test2" \
 -H "Authorization: Bearer your-secret-token"




//////////////json




POST update json file:

curl -X POST "http://91.216.104.8:5000/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-secret-token" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "storeId: ghasem" \
  -H "filename: aboutlg.json" /
  -d '{"key": "value"}'


Get the content of the json:

curl -X GET "http://91.216.104.8:5000/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-secret-token" \
  -H "storeId: ghasem" \
  -H "filename: aboutlg.json"



GET list json files:

curl -X GET "http://62.3.42.11:5002/json/storemdbrstve5d4941" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-secret-token"